From: =?UTF-8?q?Luk=C3=A1=C5=A1=20Karas?= <lukas.karas@centrum.cz>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 07:43:33 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] xmp: parse GPS coordinates locale-independently

gps_coordinate_dup() used atof(), which is locale-dependent and parses
the '.'-formatted minutes as 0 in decimal-comma locales (e.g. cs_CZ),
corrupting the coordinate. Use g_ascii_strtod() instead.
---
 src/extractor/utils/tracker-xmp.c | 10 ++++++++--
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/extractor/utils/tracker-xmp.c b/src/extractor/utils/tracker-xmp.c
index 37945a9c9..2e9d0ffbc 100644
--- a/src/extractor/utils/tracker-xmp.c
+++ b/src/extractor/utils/tracker-xmp.c
@@ -142,8 +142,14 @@ gps_coordinate_dup (const gchar *coordinates)
 		min = g_match_info_fetch (info, 2);
 		ref = g_match_info_fetch (info, 3);
 
-		d = atof (deg);
-		m = atof (min);
+		/* Use g_ascii_strtod() instead of atof(): the coordinate
+		 * components always use '.' as decimal separator, but atof()
+		 * is locale-dependent and would parse e.g. "0.956" as 0 in
+		 * locales using a decimal comma, silently dropping the
+		 * fractional minutes.
+		 */
+		d = g_ascii_strtod (deg, NULL);
+		m = g_ascii_strtod (min, NULL);
 
 		r = d + m/60;
 
